You should be getting field relative states instead of however you’ve been doing it now. Do you happen to have a codebase ? I could look and provide better input.

something like : ChassisSpeeds speeds = ChassisSpeeds.fromFieldRelativeSpeeds( translation.getX(), translation.getY(), rotation, currentHeading);

SwerveModule[    ] modStates = swerveKinematics.toSwerveModuleStates(speeds);

the difference between this and robot relative is :

ChassisSpeeds speeds = new ChassisSpeeds( translation.getX(), translation.getY(), rotation);

You will want to also apply some limitations to your modules by utilizing a max speed :

SwerveDriveKinematics.desaturateWheelSpeeds( modStates, maxSpeed);

then for each module in that array “apply” or set your desired states. This would be dependent on the vendor your motors are from.
